description:
Chapter 2: This should be better than Chapter 1...I hope.
-----------------------
Krystal's POV
I woke up to my ears popping like crazy. It was so much pain; this is what I hate about flying. I never get used to the popping. It was like my ears were getting ready to fall off the sides of my head! When the plane landed, I held my ears and tried not to cry. Vic noticed and helped me through it. She took out the ear drops and put them in my ears. I'm the only one she uses it on; the others are used to the popping. We collected our luggage and headed to our hotel. All we did was set our luggage in our rooms, ate some breakfast, and rested until 5pm. Our manager, David, woke us up and took us to the arena that the concert will be held. I quickly changed into this: http://www.polyvore.com/krystal_outfit/template?id=354459 
We drove over to the arena and quickly rehearsed the songs and dance routines. It was 7:30 by the time we finished. We were pushed to hair, makeup, and wardrobe. The arena filled with thousands of fans chanting our names. I took a deep breath and walked to my place on stage. The lights flashed on and the stage was lit and our fans were going crazy. 
Harry's POV
we drove to the arena where the concert was being held. Louis was talking about he was looking forward to the concert and thinking about going backstage to meet the group in person. I wasn't sure about anything right now, I've never heard of this group and I'm expected to go see them preform live. When we arrived, girls saw that we were here and ran over to us. We were able to make our way to the front and get in. Luckily, the security guards had teenage daughters. They let us in with no questions. Louis forced us to get close up front, it was dark. Bright lights lit up the whole arena and five girls stood on stage in the cutest clothes you'll ever see a girl wear. Music started to play and one by one they started singing and dancing (http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=euEUR_kYABI). The one with the blue pants caught my eye. She was full of energy and had an amazing voice. The way she flipped her long, dark brown hair was cute. Her smile kept me smiling, and the way she moved her flawless figure to the beat was attractive. I could hear Louis fangirling...erm...fanboying, I guess? He screamed out their names. I'm thinking of using Louis' love for them as a one way ticket to meeting them. When the concert was over, after them singing 9 more songs, we were leaving. I taped on Louis' shoulder, 
"Aren't you going backstage?" I asked. He shook his head no. 
"The girls are tired. Besides, I can't go alone." He replied. I stood there,
"I can go with you. I know how much you love them so...I can meet them with you, you know." I offered. He looked at me with a smirk on his face, 
"You fancy one of them, don't you? Come on...tell me!" he figured out, I blushed.
"The one with the long dark brown hair and gorgeous smile," I replied looking at the ground. 
"Krystal? No problem, Tommo the match maker is here. You got me my Eleanor, now I'm going to get you your Krystal." He said and pulled me to the security guards guarding the backstage entrance. We stood face to face with the two large guards.
 "Hello, I'm Louis Tomlinson and this is Harry Styles. We are in the band One Direction. We were wondering if we could meet the girls of F(x) backstage." Louis said with no fear guards looked at each other then back down to us. They stepped aside to let us through
"Thank You!" Louis called while we ran through. It wasn't hard to find the girls. Louis quickly spotted one of them and pulled me to her. We were face to face to with the beautiful girl I have ever seen...Krystal.
title: Just You: A Harry Styles Love Story Chapter 2

  PODOFRESH Balsamo Emolliente:
Cosmetico ad azione emolliente,ideale per i piedi con pelle secca e fragile che tende a screpolarsi e ad ispessirsi.

PRINCIPI ATTIVI 
Mentil Lattato: dalle spiccate proprietà rinfrescanti che dona sollievo.
Olio essenziale di Limone: esplica un'azione battericida, astringente, rinfrescante e l'essenza è altamente aromatizzante.
Estratto di ippocastano: svolge un'azione altamente protettiva, disarrossante e schiarente.
Estratto di Mirtillo: particolarmente utile nelle preparazioni destinate al trattamento di pelli sensibili. Possiede note proprietà lenitive e protettive.
Acqua distillata di Amamelide: aiuta a reattivare la circolazione cutanea e ha proprietà rinfrescanti.
Olio essenziale di Menta: possiede un notevole potere antisettico e dermopurificante e un marcato effetto rinfrescante e deodorante.
Gel di Alghe Rosse: ha ottime qualità idratanti, protettive, filmogeni e ammorbidenti.

TEXTURE 
Cosmetico in fresco balsamo di facile assorbimento, non unge.

RISULTATI ESTETICI 
Restituisce elasticità e morbidezza,prevenendo la formazione di piaghe, vesciche,duroni e callosità.

METODO D'USO 
Applicare il balsamo su piedi puliti e asciutti, senza dimenticare gli spazi interditali, massaggiare prima il dorso e poi la pianta del piede fino alle caviglie, con movimenti dolci, dal basso verso l'alto, insistendo sui punti più soggetti a screpolature e ispessimenti cutanei. Concludere il massaggio trattando singolarmente le dita.
title: Dr.Mullerk PodoFresh Balsamo Massaggio Piedi Professionale 150ml DM0030

description:
Trust is good, control is better!

We at CYBEX accept our responsibility and are happy to have the trust you place in us confirmed by independent tests. Conducting more than 200 crash tests a year and continually introducing numerous technical developments, CYBEX clearly gives safety top priority. CYBEX clearly gives safety top priority.  This explains why the current child safety seats from CYBEX score only good or very good results in the most important European safety and consumer tests.

DOUBLE SAFETY

As a Group I seat with safety pillow the CYBEX Pallas-fix offers enhanced safety compared to conventional five-point harness systems. A simple conversion turns the Group I seat into the award winning Group II/III seat CYBEX Solution X2-fix. Similar to a side airbag the new side protection pads absorb the energy of a collision at an early stage, further improving side impact protection.

2 SEATS IN ONE

In Group I, the CYBEX Pallas 2-fix features a new safety cushion system and as a 2-in-1 seat offers extremely long usability of approximately 11 years. The seat converts easily at the age of approximately 3 years (15 kg) into the CYBEX Solution X2-fix (Group II/III). The ISOFIX Connect System offers enhanced safety and greater stability in both groups.

ADJUSTABLE SAFETY CUSHION FOR MAXIMUM PROTECTION

The newly designed safety cushion adjusts forwards and backwards and offers more freedom of movement of the upper body as well as maximum safety especially in front impacts when compared to conventional five-point harness systems. The forces of a collision are distributed over the safety cushion and reduced by its impact absorbing materials. This system resembles a blown up airbag and helps to reduce the forces significantly in case of an accident. The belt does not injure the child while at the same time his or her sensitive neck and shoulder area is protected.

COMFORTABLE RECLINE FUNCTION

In Group I the Pallas-fix child seat features an easy to operate recline function which can be operated with only one hand from the front of the seat.

LINEAR SIDE IMPACT PROTECTION (L.S.P. SYSTEM)

In the further improved L.S.P. System (Linear.Side-impact.Protection) of the Pallas 2-fix the forces of a side impact collision are systematically absorbed in a linear series of reactions including the protective pillow, the side as well as head protectors. At the same time the body's kinetic energy caused by the impact is absorbed at a very early stage and the head is actively led into a safe position.

ISOFIX CONNECT

The ISOFIX Connect system offers enhanced safety and greater stability in both groups.  The seat's connectors simply snap into the vehicle's ISOFIX anchorage points. The connectors can be easily folded away making the seat compatible also with cars not equipped with ISOFIX.

Car compatibility check:

http://cybex-online.com/site/uk/carseats/pallas2-fix/type-list.html
title: CYBEX PALLAS 2-FIX - A MATTER OF TRUST

description:
Principal Dancer, Nehemiah Kish, on dancing the role of Solor and working with choreographer Natalia Makarova for La Bayadère. Find out more at http://www.roh.org.uk/productions/la-bayadere-by-natalia-makarova

Read the news feature - http://www.roh.org.uk/news/watch-nehemiah-kish-on-la-bayadere

Marius Petipa's exotic La Bayadère was given its premiere at the Bolshoi Theatre in St Petersburg in 1877. It was regularly performed within the former Soviet Union throughout the 20th century but was almost unknown in the West until 1961, when the touring Kirov Ballet performed the famous Kingdom of the Shades scene. Natalia Makarova saw the ballet as a child in Leningrad and created this version for American Ballet Theatre in 1980.

Legendary India provides the setting for a tale of love, murder and vengeful judgement by the gods, set to a lyrical score by Ludwig Minkus. The choreography provides powerful moments for the two opposing ballerinas -- the beautiful temple dancer, Nikiya, and her jealous rival, Gamzatti -- while a bronze idol comes vividly to life in a stunning solo. La Bayadère's most frequently performed sequence is the dream-like Kingdom of the Shades, when a mesmerizing procession of ballerinas dance in unison across a moonlit stage. Opulent designs by Yolanda Sonnabend perfectly fit the ballet's fevered exoticism.
title: Nehemiah Kish and Hikaru Kobayashi in rehearsals for La Bayadère (The Royal Ballet)

This fresh producer has made an impression with his previous releases on the label - his bouncing tech style going down a treat.

This latest project takes things up a level, with 'Saving Myself' being a very accessible and fun slice of Tech - all pretty standard until that crazy sax riff comes in and takes this to another level altogether. Ultimately this breaks down into a fittingly quirky vocal before it moves into a phenominal build.

description:
Malaika ad Arusha (Tanzania). One of the most urgent and poignant problems in Tanzania is the abandonment of very young babies and children, either through the parent's lack of resources or as a result of the increasing problem of HIV-AIDS and Malaria. Moved by this daunting fact and their love for children Francesca Aimone and Jutta Kassam (two Tanzanian residence) launched into voluntary work with various local orphanages.

Seeing the overwhelming need they soon hatched a plan to launch their own sheltered home. Building on their locally gained experience, Francesca and Jutta founded Malaika Children's Home in December 2004. Malaika is located in Moshono (8km from Arusha).

It now cares for children, from a few months old onwards, neglected by their families and left to fend for themselves or worse. Malaika provides the children with schooling; medical attention and most importantly LOVE -- in a stable and loving, home environment. All Malaika personnel, including 'House Mothers,' Nurses, Teachers and the office coordinators are hand picked locally, encouraging awareness as well as offering employment, regular training and professional development within the local community.

Malaika (meaning Angel in Swahili) currently cares for children assigned them by Tanzania's Social Services. Malaika's warmth and vibrancy is reflected in the faces of all the children -- full of bubbling affection and newfound confidence. They simply love welcoming and interacting with visitors. Their infectious laughter and personalities will leave you with a warm glow and an unforgettable memory.

Malaika is supported in Italy by MAISHA, an NGO started in 2005, in Padua. Through our close relationship with Maisha we have started a program through which everyone can contribute to help our children have a better future.

There are many foundations helping children in Africa. But the difference is that our priority above all, IS TO LISTEN. We don't want just to help; we want to listen, learn and contribute to an African way of life, full of its own traditions and wisdom, which is huge part of our children's heritage.

Cultural colonialism and paternalism of "Third world aids" are unknown to us. A two-way relationship of communication and teaching/learning IS OUR FOCUS. It is extremely important to us to closely follow our children growing up, so we can learn to look though their eyes. To see the dreams and the hopes they have in their little hearts.

We too have a dream, that they can become free and independent individuals in their own right in their own country, rather than being labeled as "helped" people.

We pay great attention to how they grow up day by day, respecting their culture and their country, whilst also inspiring enthusiasm in their lives, and a newborn confidence and a smile.

What drives us is the knowledge that there is nothing more important in life than to 'GIVE HOPE' and above all to give love to these children -- who previously only knew abandonment and desperation since their early years or first moments.

For these reasons alone please help our cause and be a part of a new free and promising world.

TALK ABOUT MALAIKA

Your voice is our pedestal. Talk about Malaika to everyone you know and ignite a chain reaction. SHARE OUR DREAM WITH OTHERS. Our biggest strength is through every visitor to our site talking ABOUT US. Your word of mouth is our strength and future. THANK YOU FOR CARING. http://www.malaikachildren.org
title: gita al mare di Malaika ad Arusha

Thanks for an awesome year! Twitter: @stuart_edge
Follow Breea: http://bit.ly/BreeaFB
Follow Christian: http://on.fb.me/1asBZV3

Feel free to send me stuff!
PO Box 970428
Orem, UT 84097-0428

Want me to come speak at your school or business? Email me here: stuartedgetalks@gmail.com

Filmed by Miles from "Totally Rad": http://bit.ly/MilesTR
Spencer Edge (my brother) and Corey Crowfoot (a friend) came and helped as well!

All year, people were asking me what I was going to do for Mistletoe Part 2. I didn't want to just "remake" the video, so I had to think how I was going to take the video that everyone loved, and add something to it. I don't even know how I come up with the idea, but pretty soon, I was making plans to go to Arizona and make it snow. I was going to do it in Utah, but we get so much snow here, it's not even funny. I knew going to a place where it never snowed, would make it and even better video. With the help of some friends (Miles from "Totally Rad", Spencer Edge, Breea, and Corey Crowfoot) we packed up my car and took the 11 hour road trip to Arizona State University. To our surprise (and fortune) we were there the same weekend as a big ASU football game. That helped, cause that gave us more people to talk to. We met up with Christian from "Right This Minute" while we were down there. She heard we were coming and said she would love to help out. 
This video now makes it on the top of my all time favorite videos. The reactions are priceless, and so unique. I love how you can see the snow coming before the person can, so it makes you feel like you are really part of the prank. Making it snow was so hard. We had to pray really hard every time, and ask for it...just kidding...we had a snow machine. We tested out a bunch of different methods and the snow machine was the best.
Thank you so much for watching my videos and helping me follow my dreams. It's an honor to be in contact with such awesome people!

I am planning on visiting you! I have been making plans to travel all around filming videos. Follow me on Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram to know where I will be headed next.

The lecture "Laser Irradiation in Periodontal Therapy: What Are the Goals and What Can We Achieve," by Dr. George Romanos, was part of the Dental Hygiene Forum of the 35th annual USC Periodontal and Implant Symposium (theme: "The Age of Speed") held in Los Angeles in 2010.

Dr. Romanos is a professor of clinical dentistry at the University of Rochester, NY, and director of the Unit of Laser Dentistry. He received his training in periodontics, prosthodontics and oral surgery in Germany. He previously served as associate professor for oral surgery and implantology in Frankfurt, Germany, and as a professor of implant dentistry at New York University. He is chairman of the World Federation of Laser Dentistry (WFLD), North American Division, and a member of the editorial boards of the "International Journal of Oral & Maxillofacial Implants" (IJOMI), "Clinical Implant Dentistry and Related Research," the "Journal of Prosthodontics" and "Implant Dentistry." He has written more than 170 publications and three books on lasers and immediate loading, and has given more than 500 presentations worldwide.

The Herman Ostrow School of Dentistry of USC's Office of Continuing Oral Health Professional Education (www.uscdentalce.org) has the mission of promoting excellent training and the highest standards of oral health care nationally and internationally. Through its state-of-the art program, the continuing education office offers a wide array of comprehensive courses and lifelong learning experiences for general dentists, specialists and allied professionals.

For more information, or to order the entire presentation, please contact the USC Office of Continuing Oral Health Professional Education at 213-821-2127 or cedental@usc.edu, or visit www.uscdentalce.org (CE Store).

Visit the Ostrow School of Dentistry of USC Web site at http://dentistry.usc.edu/

description:
Former President George W. Bush took the Ice Bucket Challenge, and challenged former President Bill Clinton to do it next.

The viral Ice Bucket Challenge campaign has raised more than $40 million for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), or Lou Gehrig’s disease, to the ALS Association, which will go toward finding treatments and a cure for ALS as well as for providing support to people with the disease.

Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) is a progressive neurodegenerative disease that affects nerve cells in the brain and the spinal cord. ALS attacks the motor neurons that provide voluntary movements and muscle power, according to the ALS Association.

The exact cause of ALS has not yet been determined but glutamate poisoning is a popular theory suggested by researchers at Johns Hopkins University. Glutamate is an amino acid that acts as a neurotransmitter, allowing motor neurons to communicate with one another. Glutamate is supposed to be cleaned by a cell membrane protein after transmitting a message. Researchers suggest ALS patients don’t have enough of that protein. 

Glutamate clogs the space between the nerve endings, causing motor neurons to degenerate over time. As motor neurons degenerate, they can no longer send impulses to the muscle fibers, causing muscles to atrophy.

Initial symptoms of ALS often include increasing muscle weakness, especially the arms and legs. Patients in the later stages of the disease may become totally paralyzed.

This animation explains how ALS affects the human body.
